Package org.activebpel.rt.bpel.impl.activity

This package contains classes used in the implementation model for the BPEL activities.

See:
          Description

Interface Summary
IAeCopyFromParent Interface used to set from copy operation, needed in handling virtual copy operations.
IAeEventParent Interface for picks and eventHandlers.
IAeLoopControl Tagging interface for the loop controls continue and break that is used as a param to the onContinue and onBreak methods to indicate the source of the loop control that caused the change.
IAeMessageDispatcher Interface created by message receivers in order to handle the dispatching of message or faults to the message receiver.
IAeMessageReceiverActivity Provides an interface for an activity (receive, onMessage, or onEvent) that gets queued and receives messages or faults.
IAeScopeTerminationStrategy BPEL4WS 1.1 and WS-BPEL have different strategies for terminating a scope.
IAeVariableContainer Provides method for adding a variable to an impl.
IAeWSIOActivity interface for the web service in/out activities: receive, reply, invoke, onMessage, onEvent
 

Class Summary
AeActivityAssignImpl Implementation of the BPEL assign activity.
AeActivityAssignWSBPELImpl Assign impl for 2.0.
AeActivityBreakImpl Implementation of the break activity.
AeActivityCompensateImpl The compensate activity gets called from a fault handler or from within an already executing compensation handler.
AeActivityCompensateScopeImpl The compensateScope activity gets called from a fault handler or from within an already executing compensation handler.
AeActivityContinueImpl Implementation of the continue activity.
AeActivityEmptyImpl Implementation of the bpel empty activity.
AeActivityFlowImpl Implementation of the bpel flow activity.
AeActivityForEachImpl Provides the ability to loop over a list of document elements through the use of a start and final counter value which are evaluated from expressions at execution time.
AeActivityForEachParallelImpl An extension of the forEach activity that executes all of its iterations in parallel.
AeActivityIfImpl Implementation of the bpel 2.0 if activity.
AeActivityImpl Base class for bpel activity implementations.
AeActivityInvokeImpl Implementation of the bpel invoke activity.
AeActivityOnEventScopeImpl Special version of a scope that appears within a WS-BPEL onEvent.
AeActivityPickImpl Implementation of the bpel pick activity.
AeActivityReceiveImpl Implementation of the bpel receive activity.
AeActivityRepeatUntilImpl Implementation of the bpel repeatUntil activity.
AeActivityReplyImpl Implementation of the bpel reply activity.
AeActivityRethrowImpl Implements an activity that will rethrow the current fault.
AeActivityScopeImpl Implementation of the bpel scope activity.
AeActivitySequenceImpl Implementation of the bpel sequence activity.
AeActivitySuspendImpl Implementation of the suspend activity.
AeActivityTerminateImpl Implementation of the bpel terminate activity.
AeActivityThrowImpl Implementation of the bpel throw activity.
AeActivityValidateImpl Implementation of the BPEL validate activity.
AeActivityWaitImpl Implementation of the bpel wait activity.
AeActivityWhileImpl Implementation of the bpel while activity.
AeDynamicScopeCreator Creates one or more child scope instances for a parallel forEach, onEvent, or onAlarm.
AeImplPathParallelVisitor Extension of the location path visitor that creates a custom path for the root scope of the forEach/onEvent.
AeLocationPathImplVisitor Visits each of the implementation objects and sets a custom location path and id on each object.
AeLoopActivity Base class for the while and forEach activities.
AeLoopControl A base class for the loop control activities "break" and "continue"
AeMultiStartHelper A Helper class to check if the receive or onMessage that is about to execute is part of a multi-start pattern.
AeWSIOActivityImpl Base class for some of the WSIO activities.
 

Exception Summary
AeActivityForEachImpl.AeUnsignedIntException internal exception thrown from evaluateUnsignedIntegerExpression

This package contains classes used in the implementation model for the BPEL activities.
